### Claude code
# They cover Claude Code's internal state
# and per-developer configuration.

# Claude Code internal state
.claude/worktrees/
.claude/projects/
.claude/cache/

# Per-developer Claude Code settings (paths to test data, etc.)
.claude/settings.local.json

# Observability logs (append-only JSONL; quarterly /audit-bundle reads them)
.claude/observability/

# User-scoped agent memory: perf-analyst's observations are tied to
# specific hardware/kernel/BIOS/conditions and don't generalize across
# the team. The other agent-memory files (project-scoped) ARE tracked.
.claude/agent-memory/perf-analyst.md

# Profile captures
*cpu_profile*.bin
*.prof

# Notes area used by Claude Code skills and slash commands.
# Claude is free to write into these subdirectories without triggering
# protected-path hooks; gitignoring them keeps experimental work and
# feature-spec drafts out of git status.
notes/**
notes/scratch/
notes/*/spec.md
notes/*/kickoff.md
notes/*/*.draft.md

# Feature worktrees created by /spec when the user opts in.
# The directory is bundle-protected (via .claude/protected_paths.txt)
# so the agent cannot accidentally edit a worktree's contents from the
# main checkout, and gitignored here so worktree state does not appear
# in `git status` of the main checkout.
.worktrees/

